WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:03.079
This evening, 1 Corinthians chapter number 11,

00:00:03.079 --> 00:00:05.360
1 Corinthians chapter number 11.

00:00:05.360 --> 00:00:07.199
And Brother Mark, it's always hard to prepare

00:00:07.199 --> 00:00:09.380
for a message on Mother's Day evening

00:00:09.380 --> 00:00:10.539
and Father's Day evening,

00:00:10.539 --> 00:00:13.399
because you don't know how much time you're gonna have

00:00:13.399 --> 00:00:15.819
and how many men are gonna show up,

00:00:15.819 --> 00:00:18.319
how many ladies are gonna show up to pick favorites.

00:00:18.319 --> 00:00:21.120
And I think on Mother's Day, I had about 11 minutes

00:00:21.120 --> 00:00:24.280
and tonight I got almost a full time slot, amen.

00:00:24.280 --> 00:00:25.440
Praise the Lord.

00:00:25.440 --> 00:00:27.920
Except that means we need more men, amen.

00:00:27.959 --> 00:00:30.059
And praise the Lord.

00:00:30.059 --> 00:00:33.259
1 Corinthians chapter 11, the Apostle Paul, of course,

00:00:33.259 --> 00:00:36.400
is writing to a church here, the church at Corinth.

00:00:36.400 --> 00:00:38.200
And if you know anything about the Bible,

00:00:38.200 --> 00:00:42.020
you know that the church of Corinth is not a model church.

00:00:42.020 --> 00:00:43.860
The church in Corinth had many issues.

00:00:43.860 --> 00:00:46.240
In fact, we understand as you begin reading

00:00:46.240 --> 00:00:49.680
the book of 1 Corinthians, that the church was carnal.

00:00:49.680 --> 00:00:52.400
The church was spiritually immature.

00:00:52.400 --> 00:00:54.080
And we find that the Apostle Paul,

00:00:54.080 --> 00:00:57.040
there were times in which he even said

00:00:57.040 --> 00:00:59.599
that he desired to share things with them,

00:00:59.599 --> 00:01:03.599
but they were not capable of receiving those things

00:01:03.599 --> 00:01:06.480
because they were spiritually immature.

00:01:06.480 --> 00:01:08.599
Now we understand that as the people of God,

00:01:08.599 --> 00:01:11.260
that God's design and God's plan

00:01:11.260 --> 00:01:14.400
is that we would grow spiritually,

00:01:14.400 --> 00:01:17.559
that we would come to that place of spiritual maturity.

00:01:17.559 --> 00:01:21.120
It's not a situation in which we will arrive one day

00:01:21.120 --> 00:01:24.480
for we constantly seek to draw closer

00:01:24.480 --> 00:01:26.459
and closer to our Savior.

00:01:26.459 --> 00:01:27.760
But we understand that this church

00:01:27.760 --> 00:01:29.519
was having some difficulties,

00:01:29.519 --> 00:01:31.900
and there was divisions and schisms

00:01:31.900 --> 00:01:34.019
and all sorts of things that were taking place.

00:01:34.019 --> 00:01:38.500
And I would say, understanding the culture

00:01:38.500 --> 00:01:40.180
there in the church at Corinth,

00:01:40.180 --> 00:01:43.660
that this church was in need of encouragement,

00:01:43.660 --> 00:01:46.919
but they were also in need of instruction.

00:01:46.919 --> 00:01:49.580
We could also say they were in need of correction.

00:01:49.580 --> 00:01:51.220
And the Apostle Paul provides,

00:01:51.220 --> 00:01:52.900
under the inspiration of the Holy Spirit of God

00:01:52.900 --> 00:01:55.760
in the book of 1 Corinthians, all of those things.

00:01:55.800 --> 00:01:57.400
He corrects them about some things,

00:01:57.400 --> 00:01:59.559
he gives them instruction about some things,

00:01:59.559 --> 00:02:02.059
he provides them some encouragement.

00:02:02.059 --> 00:02:04.360
And I'm thankful that for each of us,

00:02:04.360 --> 00:02:07.680
as we open the Bible, as we open the word of God,

00:02:07.680 --> 00:02:09.960
that God is able to take this word

00:02:09.960 --> 00:02:12.000
that is quick and powerful and sharper

00:02:12.000 --> 00:02:13.479
than any two-edged sword,

00:02:13.479 --> 00:02:15.979
he's able to take this word that is alive,

00:02:15.979 --> 00:02:20.059
that is profitable, and he's able to provide you and me

00:02:20.059 --> 00:02:24.000
with encouragement, with instruction, with correction.

00:02:24.000 --> 00:02:25.639
It's amazing as we open the Bible

00:02:25.639 --> 00:02:29.600
and God will meet the very needs of his people

00:02:29.600 --> 00:02:31.679
through his precious word.

00:02:31.679 --> 00:02:35.820
And I'm so thankful that God has given to us a Bible.

00:02:35.820 --> 00:02:37.880
Now, this church in Corinth here,

00:02:37.880 --> 00:02:41.240
they did not have a full Bible like we have.

00:02:41.240 --> 00:02:43.720
In fact, if you read 1 Corinthians 13,

00:02:43.720 --> 00:02:46.600
you'll read there specifically how God is talking

00:02:46.600 --> 00:02:50.139
about the fact that the Bible has not yet been complete.

00:02:50.139 --> 00:02:52.479
When that which is perfect is come,

00:02:52.479 --> 00:02:54.679
then that which is in part will be done away.

00:02:54.679 --> 00:02:57.399
And he's talking about the full canon of scripture

00:02:57.399 --> 00:02:59.759
there in 1 Corinthians 13.

00:02:59.759 --> 00:03:01.699
And so we find that this church,

00:03:01.699 --> 00:03:04.419
they were not able to, like we are,

00:03:04.419 --> 00:03:07.759
just go and grab their full Bible and read

00:03:07.759 --> 00:03:10.839
and be instructed and encouraged and corrected.

00:03:10.839 --> 00:03:12.759
But we find that the apostle Paul,

00:03:12.759 --> 00:03:16.160
God would use him to meet the needs

00:03:16.160 --> 00:03:17.720
of this particular church.

00:03:17.720 --> 00:03:20.779
And I'm thankful that the apostle Paul

00:03:20.820 --> 00:03:22.860
was a man that was faithful.

00:03:22.860 --> 00:03:25.220
He was a man that was willing to do

00:03:25.220 --> 00:03:27.339
what God had called him to do.

00:03:27.339 --> 00:03:30.059
He was surrendered to the will of God.

00:03:30.059 --> 00:03:32.220
We find that after his conversion,

00:03:32.220 --> 00:03:33.919
it seems quite obvious as you study

00:03:33.919 --> 00:03:36.100
through the New Testament that the apostle Paul

00:03:36.100 --> 00:03:39.380
had that recognition that I am crucified with Christ.

00:03:39.380 --> 00:03:42.860
He declares that in Galatians 2 in verse number 20,

00:03:42.860 --> 00:03:45.460
and he lived that way.

00:03:45.460 --> 00:03:47.759
And he was willing to follow the Lord

00:03:47.759 --> 00:03:51.919
and surrender to his will for his life.

00:03:51.919 --> 00:03:54.119
And I'm so thankful for the example.

00:03:54.119 --> 00:03:55.679
As we come to verse number one

00:03:55.679 --> 00:03:58.279
of 1 Corinthians chapter number 11,

00:03:58.279 --> 00:03:59.919
and it's just a single verse of scripture

00:03:59.919 --> 00:04:01.399
that we're gonna look at this evening.

00:04:01.399 --> 00:04:02.720
But notice what the Bible says

00:04:02.720 --> 00:04:04.960
as Paul again is writing to this church.

00:04:04.960 --> 00:04:08.000
He says to these individuals, to these believers,

00:04:08.000 --> 00:04:09.600
we know that a church is made up

00:04:09.600 --> 00:04:13.639
of born again baptized believers.

00:04:13.639 --> 00:04:16.239
And the Bible says that he's writing to them and says,

00:04:16.320 --> 00:04:21.320
be ye followers of me, even as I also am of Christ.

00:04:25.640 --> 00:04:27.700
As we're gonna think about that word example,

00:04:27.700 --> 00:04:29.679
and he says here, be followers of me,

00:04:29.679 --> 00:04:31.040
even as I also am of Christ.

00:04:31.040 --> 00:04:33.040
And I've titled the message this evening,

00:04:33.040 --> 00:04:38.040
an example worth following, an example worth following.

00:04:38.160 --> 00:04:40.880
You know, there's some bad examples out there.

00:04:40.880 --> 00:04:44.880
In fact, in many arenas of life this evening,

00:04:44.880 --> 00:04:47.640
if people were to talk about their heroes or their mentors,

00:04:47.640 --> 00:04:49.579
those individuals that they would look up to,

00:04:49.579 --> 00:04:52.079
many of them are poor examples.

00:04:52.079 --> 00:04:55.160
We find the Bible, the apostle Paul says,

00:04:55.160 --> 00:04:59.440
be followers of me, even as I also am of Christ.

00:04:59.440 --> 00:05:01.760
We're gonna think about that idea of an example

00:05:01.760 --> 00:05:04.200
and being an example worth following.

00:05:04.200 --> 00:05:05.079
What is an example?

00:05:05.079 --> 00:05:06.720
It's a pattern.

00:05:06.720 --> 00:05:10.440
We think about it this way, it is that which is proposed,

00:05:10.440 --> 00:05:14.700
notice this, to be imitated, to be imitated.

00:05:15.519 --> 00:05:17.619
Now, I want you to think about it in that context.

00:05:17.619 --> 00:05:22.619
How comfortable are you if people imitate your behavior?

00:05:24.399 --> 00:05:25.239
Amen?

00:05:25.239 --> 00:05:29.320
If they imitate exactly what you do and how you do,

00:05:29.320 --> 00:05:31.820
and by the way, kids are good at that, aren't they?

00:05:31.820 --> 00:05:33.820
Amen, you think about Father's Day today,

00:05:33.820 --> 00:05:35.420
and you think about children.

00:05:35.420 --> 00:05:36.820
Children are watching.

00:05:36.820 --> 00:05:38.399
