00:05:39.239 --> 00:05:41.940
They're listening when you don't know that they're listening.

00:05:41.940 --> 00:05:44.600
And all of a sudden, you hear children doing something,

00:05:45.320 --> 00:05:47.119
you observe their behavior, and you say,

00:05:47.119 --> 00:05:50.119
man, that looks a lot like their example,

00:05:50.119 --> 00:05:52.079
their parent, whomever that might be.

00:05:52.079 --> 00:05:55.119
Sometimes, your children could imitate your behavior,

00:05:55.119 --> 00:05:57.119
and it could be an embarrassment.

00:05:57.119 --> 00:05:58.399
Amen?

00:05:58.399 --> 00:06:00.200
And then the parent says, where did you learn that?

00:06:00.200 --> 00:06:02.019
And everybody else in the room knows exactly

00:06:02.019 --> 00:06:03.940
where they learned that, you know what I'm saying?

00:06:03.940 --> 00:06:06.760
And what I'm saying this evening is the apostle Paul,

00:06:06.760 --> 00:06:09.160
he was an example worth following,

00:06:09.160 --> 00:06:13.399
that which is proposed to be imitated.

00:06:13.440 --> 00:06:15.519
So I want you to notice, as we look at this verse

00:06:15.519 --> 00:06:17.040
of Scripture this evening, I want you to notice

00:06:17.040 --> 00:06:18.000
just a couple of thoughts.

00:06:18.000 --> 00:06:21.859
Number one, notice what Paul revealed.

00:06:21.859 --> 00:06:23.399
Notice in the text of Scripture,

00:06:23.399 --> 00:06:25.720
Paul revealed something about himself.

00:06:25.720 --> 00:06:28.760
Before we look here, and oftentimes, I think the focus

00:06:28.760 --> 00:06:31.679
