00:06:42.260 --> 00:06:46.559
he says, even as I also am of Christ.

00:06:46.559 --> 00:06:48.100
What is Paul revealing to us?

00:06:48.100 --> 00:06:51.119
Well, he's revealing to us that he was a follower

00:06:51.119 --> 00:06:54.519
of Jesus Christ, that the apostle Paul had determined

00:06:54.519 --> 00:06:57.459
in his life that I'm gonna follow Jesus.

00:06:57.459 --> 00:07:00.100
We sing songs about following, we sing songs,

00:07:00.100 --> 00:07:01.420
there's a song that's very familiar,

00:07:01.420 --> 00:07:03.519
that little chorus that we sing with children

00:07:03.519 --> 00:07:05.480
in Sunday school and junior church,

00:07:05.480 --> 00:07:09.100
I have decided to follow Jesus.

00:07:09.100 --> 00:07:11.820
No turning back, no turning back, right?

00:07:11.820 --> 00:07:14.540
Though none go with me, still I will follow.

00:07:14.540 --> 00:07:17.140
The world behind me, the cross before me,

00:07:17.140 --> 00:07:19.179
and we sing that wonderful song,

00:07:19.179 --> 00:07:21.940
and we're reminded about that decision

00:07:21.940 --> 00:07:24.220
of following the Lord Jesus Christ.

00:07:24.220 --> 00:07:27.100
In fact, during the ministry, the earthly ministry

00:07:27.100 --> 00:07:29.899
