00:07:42.100 --> 00:07:45.579
And you begin to think about that wonderful example

00:07:45.579 --> 00:07:49.339
of the apostle Paul here, but he's revealing the fact

00:07:49.339 --> 00:07:53.779
that he himself was a follower of Jesus Christ.

00:07:53.779 --> 00:07:58.619
A follower is one who takes another as his guide.

00:07:58.619 --> 00:08:03.619
Notice this, in doctrines, opinions, or examples.

00:08:03.899 --> 00:08:06.239
Notice it carries with it this idea,

00:08:06.239 --> 00:08:09.859
the definition of follower is one who imitates

00:08:09.859 --> 00:08:12.579
